1
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,000
Greetings, Mr Castavilian, I take it.

2
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:23,475
Yes, Davros. An honour
to work for you, sir.

3
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:30,266
Then allow me to show you the
future of our beloved Kaled race.

4
00:00:33,390 --> 00:00:38,000
Go, my Mark III travel machine.

5
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:48,337
The war has caused
the Kaled race to mutate,

6
00:00:48,338 --> 00:00:53,282
but within this
casing we can evolve.

7
00:00:53,307 --> 00:00:58,427
We can start anew. We can
become stronger than ever.

8
00:00:58,452 --> 00:01:03,230
We will become the
supreme race in the universe!

9
00:01:04,240 --> 00:01:12,240
Observe a bonded polycarbide
shell, a ruby-ray blaster,

10
00:01:12,265 --> 00:01:19,943
and a multi-dextrous claw capable
of annihilating a million foes.

11
00:01:20,759 --> 00:01:24,000
My ultimate masterpiece of design!

12
00:01:25,809 --> 00:01:28,475
Yes, I did some research on the name, sir.

13
00:01:29,266 --> 00:01:35,038
Since we're called Kaleds, I thought our
future selves could be an anagram of Kaled.

14
00:01:35,333 --> 00:01:38,323
Like... Lekad?

15
00:01:39,498 --> 00:01:40,498
No.

16
00:01:43,549 --> 00:01:44,549
Adlek?

17
00:01:45,116 --> 00:01:46,116
No.

18
00:01:47,416 --> 00:01:48,416
Klaid?

19
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,400
No.

20
00:01:55,634 --> 00:01:56,475
Adleka?

21
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:57,000
No.

22
00:01:57,500 --> 00:02:01,063
Davros, I need your confirmation
to begin the next bombardment, sir.

23
00:02:01,088 --> 00:02:04,923
One moment. And touch
nothing. Is that understood?

24
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,000
Yes, sir.

25
00:02:12,488 --> 00:02:13,488
Adlek.

26
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:34,700
Hello.

27
00:02:36,603 --> 00:02:38,300
Just passing by because I got a bit lost.

28
00:02:39,020 --> 00:02:42,291
It's funny. Sixty minutes
ago I was this really brilliant

29
00:02:42,292 --> 00:02:45,300
woman, and now I've got
this old face back again.

30
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:47,300
I mean, why?

31
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:51,300
Why? I ask of you, my
brand new friend. Why?

32
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:54,300
You're a bit of a puzzle.

33
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:55,400
Oh.

34
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,400
Oh.

35
00:02:57,883 --> 00:02:58,883
I'm sorry.

36
00:02:59,691 --> 00:03:00,691
No...

37
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:03,400
I am so, so sorry. I think I broke this...

38
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:07,400
multi-claw adaptable...

39
00:03:07,900 --> 00:03:08,900
What is it?

40
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:11,400
Oh.

41
00:03:14,722 --> 00:03:16,400
That's a Dalek.

42
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,400
Good word.

43
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:19,900
Dalek.

44
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:21,400
Yes, that's it.

45
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:24,400
I'm lucky I wasn't exterminated.

46
00:03:24,425 --> 00:03:28,400
Exterminated? Yes. Yes. Good word. Great.

47
00:03:28,974 --> 00:03:32,874
Wait a minute. Do you mean
this is the genesis of the Daleks?

48
00:03:32,899 --> 00:03:35,400
Oh, this is the stuff.

49
00:03:35,650 --> 00:03:36,608
Thank you. Thank you.

50
00:03:36,633 --> 00:03:40,400
No, no, no. Stop it. Look. I
was never ever here. Never.

51
00:03:40,425 --> 00:03:42,550
The timelines of the
canon are rupturing. I'm just

52
00:03:42,575 --> 00:03:45,400
going to go, and you're not
going to say a word. Okay?

53
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:49,400
No, but you broke the
multi-claw adaptable thingy-majig.

54
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:51,400
Oh, yeah.

55
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:53,400
Right.

56
00:03:54,766 --> 00:03:55,766
Hold on.

57
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,400
Never here.

58
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:20,400
Ah, where were we, Mr. Cassivilian?

59
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:25,400
Ah, the splendid design of my secondary.

60
00:04:47,043 --> 00:04:49,735
I like it.

